= VectorizedVals.lookup(OrigV) + At(SameValuesCounter, OrigV);\n  if (NumOps !=
ReducedValsToOps.at(OrigV).size())\n
LocalExternallyUsedValues[StableRdxVal];\n\nThis ensures the DenseMap::at lookup
uses the same key under which the mapping was established and prevents lookup
failure when the tracked value has been RAUW\u2019ed to another Value*.\n\n5.
Conclusion:\nThe crash occurs because we update RdxVal to a RAUW-tracked value
before using it as a key in TrackedToOrig, which was populated with the pre-RAUW
pointer keys. Separating the notion of the \"original candidate key\" (for
TrackedToOrig lookups) from the \"stable current value\" (for external-use
tracking) resolves the inconsistency. This patch prevents the assertion and
correctly handles values that may be replaced between analysis/data-structure
construction and subsequent scans within tryToReduce.",
